(1, 1, '2012-06-10 17:17:51', '2012-06-10 21:17:51', 'Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!\r\n\r\nThere was a low rumbling of heavy sea-boots among the benches, and a still slighter shuffling of women''s shoes, and all was quiet again, and every eye on the preacher. He paused a little; then kneeling in the pulpit''s bows, folded his large brown hands across his chest, uplifted his closed eyes, and offered a prayer so deeply devout that he seemed kneeling and praying at the bottom of the sea. This ended, in prolonged solemn tones, like the continual tolling of a bell in a ship that is foundering at sea in a fog&amp;mdash;in such tones he commenced reading the following hymn; but changing his manner towards the concluding stanzas, burst forth with a pealing exultation and joy&amp;mdash; Nearly all joined in singing this hymn, which swelled high above the howling of the storm. A brief pause ensued; the preacher slowly turned over the leaves of the Bible, and at last, folding his hand down upon the proper page, said: "Beloved shipmates, clinch the last verse of the first chapter of Jonah&amp;mdash;''And God had prepared a great fish to swallow up Jonah.''" "Shipmates, this book, containing only four chapters&amp;mdash;four yarns&amp;mdash;is one of the smallest strands in the mighty cable of the Scriptures. Yet what depths of the soul does Jonah''s deep sealine sound! what a pregnant lesson to us is this prophet! What a noble thing is that canticle in the fish''s belly! How billow-like and boisterously grand! We feel the floods surging over us; we sound with him to the kelpy bottom of the waters; sea-weed and all the slime of the sea is about us! But WHAT is this lesson that the book of Jonah teaches? Shipmates, it is a two-stranded lesson; a lesson to us all as sinful men, and a lesson to me as a pilot of the living God. As sinful men, it is a lesson to us all, because it is a story of the sin, hard-heartedness, suddenly awakened fears, the swift punishment, repentance, prayers, and finally the deliverance and joy of Jonah. As with all sinners among men, the sin', 'Hello world! Post with long title!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-world', '', '', '2012-06-25 08:55:06', '2012-06-25 12:55:06', '', 0, 'http://fatcatch:8888/?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(4, 1, '2012-06-10 18:31:20', '2012-06-10 18:31:20', '<div id="main-text" class="clearfix">\r\n<div id="firstcol" class="acolumn"><h1><span>Design</span></h1><p class="hyphenate">All our projects are <a href="http://www.w3.org/standards/"><abbr title="World Wide Web Consortium">WC3</abbr> standards</a> compliant, making them accessible to the broadest user base and enduring in style and functionality.</p><ul><li class="hyphenate">Carefully crafted Web site designs and application interfaces that harness the latest technologies.</li><li class="hyphenate">Animation and video that enhances content, not distracts from it.</li><li class="hyphenate">Branding that makes your company stand out.</li><li class="hyphenate">User experience design that makes the machinery invisible.</li></ul></div>\r\n<div id="lastcol" class="acolumn"><h1><span>Development</span></h1><p class="hyphenate">We provide maintenance and design-to-deployment services, utilizing expertise in client side and server side technologies.</p><ul><li class="hyphenate">Customization of the most popular Content Management Systems including integration of e-commerce solutions.</li><li class="hyphenate">Performance optimization to securely speed page-loads and database calls.</li></ul></div>\r\n</div>', 'FatCatchDesign • Web Design, Development, and Programming', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cast-your-net-catch-the-web', '', '', '2013-06-08 10:12:18', '2013-06-08 14:12:18', '', 0, 'http://fatcatch:8888/?page_id=4', 0, 'page', '', 0),
